---
import { Container, TextSection } from '@components/odyssey-theme';
import Layout from '../layouts/Page.astro';

const seo = {
	title: 'Solutions | NMES for Astronauts',
	description: 'Current countermeasures and the NMES solution',
};
---

<Layout seo={seo}>
	<Container>
		<TextSection narrow>
		<h1 style="text-align: center;">
      Countermeasures: Fighting the Fade
    </h1>
		<p style="text-align: center;">
			To <strong>combat</strong> muscle loss, space agencies currently rely on one main tool: <strong>exercise</strong>. But is it enough? And what if there's a better way?
		</p>
    </TextSection>

    <section class="comparison-section">
      <div class="card traditional">
        <h2>The Status Quo: Resistive Exercise</h2>
        <p>
          Currently, the <strong>gold standard</strong> for fighting atrophy is heavy resistance training. While effective, it comes with significant costs.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Heavy Lifting:</strong> Astronauts must strap themselves into massive, vibration-isolated resistance machines (like ARED).</li>
          <li><strong>Time Consuming:</strong> It requires 2+ hours of <strong>intense</strong> physical exertion every single day, eating into valuable mission time.</li>
          <li><strong>Incomplete:</strong> Even with this rigorous schedule, some muscle loss still occurs, and the equipment is too <strong>bulky</strong> for smaller spacecraft destined for Mars.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card nmes">
        <h2>The Future: NMES</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Neuromuscular Electrical Stimulation (NMES)</strong> offers a revolutionary, complementary approach that addresses the limitations of traditional exercise. It consists of a <strong>fabric sleeve</strong> with electrodes that can both sense degradation and administer electrical stimulation.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Passive Activation:</strong> NMES applies <strong>electrical currents</strong> directly to motor nerves, eliciting involuntary muscle contractions. This mimics the mechanical stress needed to stimulate <strong>protein synthesis</strong> and attenuate atrophy [4].</li>
          <li><strong>Precision Targeting:</strong> Unlike general exercise, NMES can be tuned to target specific muscle fibers, ensuring even the deep, hard-to-reach anti-gravity muscles are engaged.</li>
          <li><strong>Efficiency:</strong> The device is the size of a smartphone. It allows astronauts to receive treatment <strong>passively</strong> while working on other tasks, saving hours of crew time.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="benefits">
          <h3>The Advantage</h3>
          <p>High-efficiency muscle preservation with zero footprint. <strong>Maintain</strong> mass without the mass.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="nav-button-container">
      <a href="/simulation" class="nav-arrow" aria-label="Next: The Simulation">
        <span class="nav-label">NEXT</span>
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line>
          <polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"></polyline>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
	</Container>
</Layout>

<style>
  .nav-button-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .nav-arrow {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--theme-on-bg);
    opacity: 0.5;
    transition: all var(--theme-transition);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .nav-arrow:hover {
    color: var(--theme-primary);
    opacity: 1;
    transform: scale(1.2);
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 5px var(--theme-primary));
  }
  .nav-arrow svg {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
  }

  .nav-arrow:hover {
    color: var(--theme-primary);
    opacity: 1;
    transform: scale(1.1);
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 5px var(--theme-primary));
  }
  .nav-arrow svg {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
  }
  .nav-label {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
  }
  .icon-header {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
    vertical-align: middle;
    color: var(--theme-primary);
  }
	.comparison-grid {
		display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .comparison-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .comparison-section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .card {
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: var(--theme-shape-radius);
    border: 1px solid var(--theme-surface-2);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-5px);
  }

  .traditional {
    background-color: var(--theme-surface-1);
  }

  .nmes {
    background-color: var(--theme-surface-2);
    border-color: var(--theme-primary);
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .limitations, .benefits {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
  }

  .limitations h3, .benefits h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }
</style>
